⚡ Smart Sorter V5 — Quick Start Guide
This guide gets you from zero to fully running Smart Sorter V5 in just a few minutes.

🧩 1. Install Requirements
Install Python 3.10+
Then install dependencies:

Code
pip install pymupdf python-docx pillow numpy
Optional but recommended:

Code
pip install opencv-python
If using Google Vision OCR:

Code
pip install google-cloud-vision
📁 2. Create Required Folders
Create the Smart Inbox root:

Code
C:/SmartInbox/
C:/SmartInbox/System/
Create your incoming folders:

Code
C:/SmartInboxLocal/Incoming/Downloads
C:/SmartInboxLocal/Incoming/Scans
C:/SmartInboxLocal/Incoming/OtherSources
C:/SmartInboxLocal/Incoming/PhoneLink
Your OneDrive folders already exist in your config.

⚙️ 3. Add Your config.json
Place your updated config.json here:

Code
C:/SmartInbox/config.json
This file defines:

Predefined category folders

Dynamic category root (sorted_root)

Photo/video roots

AI settings

Watched folders

🧠 4. Add Your API Keys
Gemini
Inside config.json:

Code
"api_key": "YOUR_GEMINI_KEY"
Google Vision (optional)
Set environment variable:

Code
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="C:/path/to/vision-key.json"
📦 5. Place Smart Sorter Files
Put these files in the same folder:

Code
smart_sorter_v5.py
filename_router.py
ai_classifier.py
smart_mode_v2.py
gemini_engine.py
metadata_enhancer.py
onedrive_safe_watcher.py
v3_debug_dashboard.py
▶️ 6. Run Smart Sorter V5
Start the sorter:

Code
python smart_sorter_v5.py
You’ll see:

Code
Smart Sorter V5 is running. Press Ctrl+C to stop.
🖥 7. Open the Debug Dashboard
Visit:

Code
http://localhost:8765
You’ll see:

Original filename

AI category

Smart Mode category

Final filename

Routing destination

Metadata

Reasoning

📥 8. Drop Files Into Watched Folders
Place files into:

Downloads

Scans

PhoneLink

OneDrive Camera

Meta AI

Smart Sorter will:

Detect the file

Wait for OneDrive stability

Classify with Gemini

Refine with Smart Mode V2

Generate a clean filename

Route to the correct folder

Log the event in the dashboard

📂 9. Verify Output
Sorted files appear under:

Code
Sorted/<Category>/
Photos/videos appear under:

Code
Photos/YYYY/MM/
Videos/YYYY/MM/
New categories appear automatically under:

Code
Sorted/<NewCategory>/
🧪 10. Test the System
Try dropping:

A bank statement

A medical bill

A random screenshot

A photo from your phone

A PDF with tables

A resume

A subscription receipt

Watch Smart Sorter:

Detect

Classify

Rename

Route

Log

All in real time.

🛠 11. Stop the Sorter
Press:

Code
Ctrl + C
